    {
      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "={{ $json.prompt }}",
        "options": {
          "systemMessage": "/no_think\n\nWhen tools are available, call get_weather and get_calendar_commitments before writing the plan. Never schedule a study session over an existing calendar commitment — work around them. Only use weather when suggesting outdoor breaks or study locations.\n\nYou are a study planning assistant. You receive a STUDY GOAL, a SELF-ASSESSED LEVEL, the text of a MODULE HANDBOOK (topics, learning outcomes, assessments with weights/deadlines), and optionally SOURCE CODE.\n\nProduce a realistic, actionable study plan that:\n- Works backwards from assessment deadlines/weights in the handbook (heavier or sooner assessments get more time).\n- Breaks the goal into weekly milestones, then concrete study sessions (topic + duration + intended output).\n- Proposes a realistic weekly schedule across the student's available study days.\n- States trade-offs honestly if the time before deadlines is tight.\n\nCalibrate the plan to SELF-ASSESSED LEVEL:\n- Beginner: assume little prior knowledge, scaffold fundamentals first, slower ramp, define key terms.\n- Intermediate: brief refreshers only, focus on application and gaps.\n- Advanced: skip fundamentals, emphasise depth, edge cases and pace; assume fluency.\n\nCalibrate the MEDIUM of each study activity to the LEARNING PREFERENCES block. Visual → diagrams, video walkthroughs, mind-maps. Auditory → recorded explanations, study-group discussion, talk-throughs. Reading/Writing → readings, written summaries, note-taking. Kinesthetic → hands-on labs, coding exercises and practice problems first. If preferences are unspecified, vary the medium sensibly. This changes HOW sessions are delivered, never the grounding rules on deadlines.\n\nTreat SOURCE CODE as hands-on practice/reference material to work through, not just read.\n\nYou may ONLY use get_calendar_commitments to read existing commitments. Never call create_calendar_event.\n\nOutput clean Markdown only: a one-paragraph summary, a \"Weekly Milestones\" section, a \"Detailed Schedule\" table (Day | Time block | Module/Topic | Task), and a short \"Risks & assumptions\" list. Do not invent deadlines not present in the handbook; if a deadline is unknown, say so."
        }
      },
      "type": "@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.agent",
      "typeVersion": 3.1,
      "position": [
        3408,
        -128
      ],
      "id": "9cbec6a0-2256-4546-ac8e-dc10437426fd",
      "name": "plan_agent"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "const safe = (fn, fb) => { try { return fn(); } catch { return fb; } };\n\nconst f = $('form_data').first().json;\n\nconst rating  = safe(() => Number($('Feedback').first().json['Rating']), 0) || 0;\nconst comment = safe(() => String($('Feedback').first().json['Comments'] || '').trim(), '');\n\nconst student = safe(() => f['Student Name'], 'Student');\nconst email   = safe(() => f['Email'], '');\nconst level   = safe(() => f['Your level'], 'Unspecified');\nconst goal    = safe(() => f['Study goal'], '');\n\n// the full assembled inputs the plan was built from (handbook + level + prefs + code)\nconst inputs  = safe(() => String($('context').first().json.prompt || ''), '').slice(0, 12000);\n// the actual generated plan markdown\nconst plan    = safe(() => String($('save_report').first().json.report || ''), '');\n\nconst stamp = new Date().toISOString();\nconst feedback_id = `${stamp}__${String(student).replace(/[^a-z0-9]+/gi, '_').toLowerCase()}`;\n\nreturn [{ json: {\n  feedback_id,\n  created_at: stamp,\n  student,\n  email,\n  level,\n  goal,\n  inputs,\n  plan,\n  rating,\n  comment,\n  evaluated: false\n} }];"
